.TH Simple_Shell 3 "14 August 2025" "Custom Version" "Simple_Shell Manpage"
.SH NAME
Simple_Shell \- our version of Simple Shell

.SH PROLOG
.B This manual page is part of the POSIX Programmer's Manual.  The
Linux implementation of this interface may differ (consult the
corresponding Linux manual page for details of Linux behavior), or
the interface may not be implemented on Linux.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include """simple_shell.h"""

.B int Simple_Shell(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Simple_Shell()
is a simplified implementation of the standard SHELL of Unix.The shell utility is a command language interpreter that shall
execute commands read from a command line string, the standard
input, or a specified file. The application shall ensure that the
commands to be executed are expressed in the language described in

Pathname expansion shall not fail due to the size of a file.

Shell input and output redirections have an implementation-defined
offset maximum that is established in the open file description.

.T
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns.
If it is an error the return will be negative.
.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
1. Execute a shell command from a string:
$ -c "ls myfile"

2. Execute a shell script from a file in the current directory:
$ my_shell_cmds
.fi
Output:
.in

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf(3)
.SH AUTHOR
Function written by ROY Mathis, KEDDOUS Heytem and GODALIER Mathieu.